{
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Conclusion",
      "items": [
        "Both allocate breach risk, but the statutory rules differ."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Points",
      "items": [
        "Article 587: Breach triggers the deposit rule.",
        "Article 588: Breach allows choosing between deposit and liquidated damages when both are agreed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Differences",
      "items": [
        "Article 587: The receiving party must return double the deposit upon breach.",
        "Article 588: When both clauses exist, the non-breaching party chooses one."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Applicable Conditions",
      "items": [
        "Article 587: A deposit is paid and a breach occurs.",
        "Article 588: Both clauses are agreed in the contract."
      ]
    },
